The paper discusses the use of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) for graph classification problems, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). However, since the paper focuses on the use of graph kernels to embed local neighborhoods of graphs in a continuous vector space, it is most likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The other sub-categories are also possible because they are related to the use of CNNs and graph classification, but they are less likely to be the primary focus of the paper.
